literals: "Select how yt-dlp chooses formats. Use '+' to combine streams, '/' for fallback."
"Expected final extension; helps detect when the file was already downloaded/converted."
"Allow unplayable formats to be extracted and downloaded."
"Useful for extracting metadata even if the video is not downloadable."
"Comma-separated list of fields to sort formats. See 'Sorting Formats' in yt-dlp docs."
"Force use of the given format_sort over default sorting."
"Prefer free containers over non-free ones of the same quality."
"Merge multiple video streams into a single file."
"Merge multiple audio streams into a single file."

"Limit the filename length (excluding extension) to the specified number of characters"
"Embed subtitles into the downloaded video file using ffmpeg."
"Comma-separated list of languages (e.g., en,es,fr). Use 'all' to download all available."
"Write metadata such as title, artist, etc. into the media file using ffmpeg."
"Download Thumbnail file in same folder as video file.\n Must select if Embed Thumbnail is selected."

"Write the full video description to a separate .description file."

"Limit number of top-level comments to fetch. Not always Work use with caution."
"Limit number of parent comments to fetch. Not always Work use with caution."
"Limit number of replies to fetch. Not always Work use with caution."
"Resume partially downloaded files instead of starting over."
"Path to a file where IDs of already downloaded videos are stored."
"Number of times to retry for a failed download."
"Number of retries for each video fragment (if segmented)."
"Limit download speed (e.g., 500K for 500 Kilobytes/sec, 2M for 2 Megabytes/sec)."
"If a video fragment is missing, skip it instead of failing."
"Continue downloading even if some downloads fail."
"Skip downloads if the file already exists."
"Allow downloading fragments in parallel to speed up downloads."
"Override the user-agent string sent with requests."
"Set a custom HTTP referer header. Useful for some sites."
"Number of seconds to sleep before each download."
"Client-side IP address to bind to for outgoing connections."
"Adds chapter markers for selected segment types (e.g. sponsor, intro) without removing them."
"Do not show error if SponsorBlock segments are not found."
"Enable SponsorBlock querying even if no removal/marking is specified."
